@TheOneNFT yup, and the blockchain-neighborhood is a dangerous placeüòÖ

5/ You could simply order a new Ledger and access your tokens with your unique 24-word recovery phrase.

God bless all of you in this space. You are all super early, and therefore all of us need to be showing each other the way. Please don't let a ~$100 cost you your assets.

4/ Key takeaways: By using i.e. a Ledger, you can keep your tokens safe. Even if you were to use the ledger, you could remain in control of the tokens, as long as you have the seed phrase - which you NEVER should share with anyone.

3/ When you own crypto/nfts, what you really own is a private key that gives you access to your coins/token. You should be the only one in control of this key ‚Äì and you need to keep it secure. With a hot wallet, you are constantly under threat.
2/ Now if the answer to that question is, "No, I wouldn't really feel safe doing that" you should look into getting a hardware wallet (Trezor or Ledger).

Security Thread/1 to all of my fellow NFT collectors.
I still meet people in this space that doesn't use cold-wallets for their extremely valuable NFTs. This is absolutely insane. Ask yourself this question: Would I be ok with walking around with $100-400k in my "backpocket"?
